00:29:14,260 --> 00:29:18,100
 and the bank, hopefully, the bank will faithfully

531
00:29:18,100 --> 00:29:21,460
 and wisely manage your money.

532
00:29:21,460 --> 00:29:23,420
 In times of need, you go to the bank

533
00:29:23,420 --> 00:29:26,100
 and you withdraw some money, right?

534
00:29:26,100 --> 00:29:28,820
 It really does not belong to the bank manager.

535
00:29:28,820 --> 00:29:32,900
 The bank manager is managing someone else's resource,

536
00:29:32,900 --> 00:29:34,740
 your resource.

537
00:29:34,740 --> 00:29:38,660
 This is the same way our relationship with God and you.

538
00:29:38,660 --> 00:29:43,660
 God entrusts something in you, in your life.

539
00:29:43,660 --> 00:29:45,980
 And you're kind of like a bank manager.

540
00:29:45,980 --> 00:29:47,540
 You're a steward.

541
00:29:47,540 --> 00:29:52,540
 And the only thing required for you is faithfulness.

542
00:29:52,540 --> 00:29:57,020
 Whether you're using all the resources as much as possible

543
00:29:57,020 --> 00:29:59,420
 to serve God and to worship Him.

544
00:29:59,420 --> 00:30:02,660
 That is biblical stewardship.

545
00:30:03,540 --> 00:30:04,820
 And do not forget that.

546
00:30:04,820 --> 00:30:08,580
 And that's what Hezekiah's story is all about.

547
00:30:08,580 --> 00:30:11,140
 Why didn't the Bible, I actually want the Bible

